name: Bendungan Latu
address: Jalan Manggis, Banjar Juwet, F6MC+3PQ, Blahkiuh, Kec. Abiansemal, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1:
Some people rated this place 3 stars for the road condition. This place is not a shopping mall, it is a dam in nature.

Let me tell you, this place is beautiful and rich of clean oxygen to breathe. You go there either for jogging or cycling, not to ride your car.

This place is set for farmers and those who praise nature. Very recommended!
review 2: Good place, but I think a dog there is dying
review 3: We came there from pundung and it was a little bit on adventurous side if you're not use to small and slippery road. There's not much to see around the bendungan though. And I would not recommend to bring young kids because not all the area got safety rails.
review 4: It's okay as its place not really for tourists destination apparently. But, overall the maps done good, spot on the location. The road is too tight for a car to get to the site, eventhou surrounded by nice padi fields.
review 5: The pathway for trekking need to be fix because at some area already broken & covered by mud & grass
